HEADWORD: Zaphrentis
<hw>Za*phren"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct genus of cyathophylloid corals
common in the Paleozoic formations. It is cup-shaped with numerous
septa, and with a deep pit in one side of the cup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zapotilla</ent>⟦br⟧
